Peru Stocks: Atacocha, Casa Grande, Ferreyros, Rio Alto, Volcan

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-05-06T21:42:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-06/peru-stocks-atacocha-casa-grande-ferreyros-rio-alto-volcan.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:10 p.m.  New York  time.  The Lima General Index surged 5.5 percent to 21,769.92. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index rose 4.4 percent to 2,829.12.  Industrial stocks gained as investors bet a weekend poll
will show presidential candidate Keiko Fujimori gaining on rival
Ollanta Humala ahead the June 5 election, said Miguel Pancorvo,
the head trader at Lima-based brokerage Compass SAB. Humala, a
former military rebel, has pledged to impose a windfall tax on
mining companies and renegotiate trade accords with nations like
the U.S. and  Canada .  Corp. Aceros Arequipa SA (CORAREI1 PE), the Lima-based
steelmaker, jumped 10 percent to 2.87 soles.  Ferreyros SA (FERREYC1) 
(FERREYC1 PE), the Lima-based distributor for Caterpillar Inc.,
climbed 9.7 percent to 3.40 soles after first-quarter net income
rose 22 percent to $15.3 million.  Casa Grande  (CASAGRC1 PE),
Peru’s largest sugar producer and a unit of Gloria SA, rose 8.5
percent to 15.30 soles.  Cementos Pacasmayo SAA (CPACASI1)  (CPACASC1 PE),
the Hochschild Group’s cement producer, gained 8 percent to 6.80
soles.  Mining stocks gained after gold and zinc advanced in New
York and  London .  Alturas Minerals Corp. (ALT)  , a Canadian gold and copper
exploration company, soared 18 percent to 20 cents. Cia. Minera
Atacocha SA (ATACOBC1 PE), the Lima-based zinc and lead
producer, jumped 16 percent to 1.24 soles. Volcan Cia. Minera
SAA (VOLCAAC1 PE), Peru’s largest silver and zinc producer,
gained 12 percent to 4.80 soles after first-quarter net income
rose 48 percent to $90.2 million.  Rio Alto Mining Ltd. (RIO)  ,
a Canadian gold exploration company, advanced 8.5 percent to
$2.17.  Minsur SA (MINSURI1)  (MINSURI1 PE), the world’s fourth-largest tin
producer, rose 7.5 percent to 4.14 soles after first-quarter net
income climbed 28 percent to $119.3 million.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Emery in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
